verses.text_plain: I am come into my garden, my sister, my spouse: I have gathered my myrrh with my spice; I have eaten my honeycomb with my honey; I have drunk my wine with my milk: eat, O friends; drink, yea, drink abundantly, O beloved.
verses.verse_html:
1I am come into my garden, my sister, my spouse: I have gathered my myrrh with my spice; I have eaten my honeycomb with my honey; I have drunk my wine with my milk: eat, O friends; drink, yea, drink abundantly, O beloved. ▼
▼ yea…: or, and be drunken with loves

footnotes.body_text: ▼ yea…: or, and be drunken with loves
footnotes.body_html: ▼ yea…: or, and be drunken with loves

verses.text_plain: I sleep, but my heart waketh: it is the voice of my beloved that knocketh, saying, Open to me, my sister, my love, my dove, my undefiled: for my head is filled with dew, and my locks with the drops of the night.
verses.verse_html: 2I sleep, but my heart waketh: it is the voice of my beloved that knocketh, saying, Open to me, my sister, my love, my dove, my undefiled: for my head is filled with dew, and my locks with the drops of the night.

verses.text_plain: I have put off my coat; how shall I put it on? I have washed my feet; how shall I defile them?
verses.verse_html: 3I have put off my coat; how shall I put it on? I have washed my feet; how shall I defile them?

verses.text_plain: My beloved put in his hand by the hole of the door, and my bowels were moved for him.
verses.verse_html:
4My beloved put in his hand by the hole of the door, and my bowels were moved for him. ▼
▼ for him: or, (as some read) in me

footnotes.body_text: ▼ for him: or, (as some read) in me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ for him: or, (as some read) in me

verses.text_plain: I rose up to open to my beloved; and my hands dropped with myrrh, and my fingers with sweet smelling myrrh, upon the handles of the lock.
verses.verse_html:
5I rose up to open to my beloved; and my hands dropped with myrrh, and my fingers with sweet smelling myrrh, upon the handles of the lock. ▼
▼ sweet…: Heb. passing, or, running about

footnotes.body_text: ▼ sweet…: Heb. passing, or, running about
footnotes.body_html: ▼ sweet…: Heb. passing, or, running about

verses.text_plain: I opened to my beloved; but my beloved had withdrawn himself, and was gone: my soul failed when he spake: I sought him, but I could not find him; I called him, but he gave me no answer.
verses.verse_html: 6I opened to my beloved; but my beloved had withdrawn himself, and was gone: my soul failed when he spake: I sought him, but I could not find him; I called him, but he gave me no answer.

tokens.text: him, but I could not find
him, but he gave me no answer

verses.text_plain: The watchmen that went about the city found me, they smote me, they wounded me; the keepers of the walls took away my veil from me.
verses.verse_html: 7The watchmen that went about the city found me, they smote me, they wounded me; the keepers of the walls took away my veil from me.

verses.text_plain: I charge you, O daughters of Jerusalem, if ye find my beloved, that ye tell him, that I am sick of love.
verses.verse_html:
8I charge you, O daughters of Jerusalem, if ye find my beloved, that ye tell him, that I am sick of love. ▼
▼ that ye: Heb. what, etc

footnotes.body_html: ▼ that ye: Heb. what, etc

verses.text_plain: What is thy beloved more than another beloved, O thou fairest among women? what is thy beloved more than another beloved, that thou dost so charge us?
verses.verse_html: 9What is thy beloved more than another beloved, O thou fairest among women? what is thy beloved more than another beloved, that thou dost so charge us?

verses.text_plain: My beloved is white and ruddy, the chiefest among ten thousand.
verses.verse_html:
10My beloved is white and ruddy, the chiefest among ten thousand. ▼
▼ the chiefest: Heb. a standard-bearer

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the chiefest: Heb. a standard-bearer

verses.text_plain: His head is as the most fine gold, his locks are bushy, and black as a raven.
verses.verse_html:
11His head is as the most fine gold, his locks are bushy, and black as a raven. ▼
▼ bushy: or, curled

verses.text_plain: His eyes are as the eyes of doves by the rivers of waters, washed with milk, and fitly set.
verses.verse_html:
12His eyes are as the eyes of doves by the rivers of waters, washed with milk, and fitly set. ▼
▼ fitly…: Heb. sitting in fulness, that is, fitly placed, and set as a precious stone in the foil of a ring

footnotes.body_text: ▼ fitly…: Heb. sitting in fulness, that is, fitly placed, and set as a precious stone in the foil of a ring
footnotes.body_html: ▼ fitly…: Heb. sitting in fulness, that is, fitly placed, and set as a precious stone in the foil of a ring

verses.text_plain: His cheeks are as a bed of spices, as sweet flowers: his lips like lilies, dropping sweet smelling myrrh.
verses.verse_html:
13His cheeks are as a bed of spices, as sweet flowers: his lips like lilies, dropping sweet smelling myrrh. ▼
▼ sweet flowers: or, towers of perfumes

footnotes.body_text: ▼ sweet flowers: or, towers of perfumes
footnotes.body_html: ▼ sweet flowers: or, towers of perfumes

verses.text_plain: His hands are as gold rings set with the beryl: his belly is as bright ivory overlaid with sapphires.
verses.verse_html: 14His hands are as gold rings set with the beryl: his belly is as bright ivory overlaid with sapphires.

verses.text_plain: His legs are as pillars of marble, set upon sockets of fine gold: his countenance is as Lebanon, excellent as the cedars.
verses.verse_html: 15His legs are as pillars of marble, set upon sockets of fine gold: his countenance is as Lebanon, excellent as the cedars.

verses.text_plain: His mouth is most sweet: yea, he is altogether lovely. This is my beloved, and this is my friend, O daughters of Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html:
16His mouth is most sweet: yea, he is altogether lovely. This is my beloved, and this is my friend, O daughters of Jerusalem. ▼
▼ mouth: Heb. palate
